HEADWORD: Self-examination
<hw>Self`-ex*am`i*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
examination into one's own state, conduct, and motives, particularly in
regard to religious feelings and duties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

